I totally understand what you're saying about seeing life through the filter of our own experiences. The problem lies within this whole society. For example education for us is just based on being able to find work one day, so education mostly helps us to earn money. Just imagine if education was centered on the individual, on the human being..helping us understand our emotions, work on them & overcome them, teaching us about our true self, the purpose of life, why we are really here etc. But this will not never happen if the majority does not question anything and just goes on living like everyone always has..just bringing about huge technological & material changes is not what make us civilised or intelligent. 

Mating, child bearing is an instinctual thing & instinct is something to be transcended if we want to go higher on the evolution ladder. 

Civil marriage is quite a recent thing and I can tell u that signing a contract goes against the very nature of our soul. I don't know for others but I don't consider myself as an object or the private property of anyone to go & sign a contract..and it goes the other way as well..no one belongs to me. Signing a contract with another human being sends a mental & emotional message to our subconscious mind.. that we own that person. That's why some people kill their spouses if they want a divorce or is seeing some else.

Marriage is the best way to raise children? Really? Then we should have so many mentally, emotionally & spiritually healthy individuals walking the surface of this earth. Then why are there so many wars, so much corruption, so much sexual assault, so much mental verbal abuse, so much inequality, so much harm being caused to this planet..these things are caused by us humans, aren't they? Most of us have been raised in marriages, then what's the problem? The problem is simply our low level of consciousness..when you get 2 unconscious people getting married, you cannot expect anything great to come out of it..those who can objectively observe people/society will definitely see it.
